                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Feb. 17: State-owned companies may soon be asked to buy atleast 20 per cent of their total purchases from micro and small medium enterprises (MSMEs). We are preparing a cabinet note to encourage the micro and small sector, said Dinesh Rai, secretary, ministry of micro, small and medium enterprises. According to the proposal, all PSUs, including the railways and entities under the defence ministry, will have to procure 20 per cent of their total requirements from MSMEs.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 17: State-run power project financier Rural Electrification Corporation (REC) today said institutional investors could revise their bid  both in terms of price and quantity  for its forthcoming follow-on-public offer.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 17: Hinduja Swiss Holding Ltd has acquired Swiss bank Banca Commerciale Lugano, which will be merged with its subsidiary Hinduja Bank (Switzerland) Ltd.                                                                                                                          
